04/10/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Two trains collided early on Monday (October 4th) at the exit of the Dragoil Railway Station in western Bulgaria.
The incident happened when a train travelling from Serbia hit another train that was carrying workers from Dragoman.
According to preliminary information, the two train drivers and at least ten other people were injured.
(bTV, Focus news agency, Darik, Novinite - 04/10/10)
